	 We use a "strict" DTD to make IE follow the alignment rules. -->
	 
<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_4.xsd">
<body class="container">
	<h3>Page Links (1)</h3>
	
	To render a link to another page, use the PageLink component. 
	It calculates the full URL at runtime and renders a link to it.
  	
  	<div class="eg">
		<t:pagelink page="examples/navigation/PageLinks2">A page link</t:pagelink><br/>
	</div>

	When clicked it sends a <strong>page render request</strong>. Click the link above to learn more.<br/><br/>

	References:	
	<a href="http://people.apache.org/~hlship/t5api/apidocs/org/apache/tapestry5/corelib/components/PageLink.html">PageLink</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/page-navigation.html">Page Navigation</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/component-rendering.html">Component Rendering</a>.<br/><br/>

	<t:pagelink page="Index">Home</t:pagelink><br/><br/>
	
